uk.ac.ebi.pride.tools.mzxml_parser

Class MzXMLFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pride.tools.mzxml_parser.MzXMLFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JMzReader

    public class MzXMLFile
extends java.lang.Object
implements JMzReader
    The main class to parse mzXML files. This objects represents a mzXML file and provides all the required functions to access the files elements.
    Author:
    jg

      • getScanByNum

        public Scan getScanByNum(java.lang.Long scanNum)
                  throws MzXMLParsingException
        Unmarshals a given scan based on its num attribute. This function can only retrieve up to level 2 scans. Scans that are contained within a scan that's contained within a scan are not accessible via this function. In case the scan is not available (either > level 2 or the number does not exist) null is returned.
        Parameters:
        scanNum - The scan's number.
        Returns:
        A Scan object or null in case the scan is not available.
        Throws:
        MzXMLParsingException

        Unmarshals a given scan based on its num attribute. This function can only retrieve up to level 2 scans.         Parameters:

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getSpectraIds()
        Description copied from interface: JMzReader
        Returns a list of Strings that hold the spectra's ids. The order of the returned ids resembls the order the spectra are returned in the spectra iterator. For formats that do not support ids such as dta or mgf the spectrum's 1-based index is used as id.
